prompt:
<s>[INST] <<SYS>>
As a log parser, you will be provided with a log message, and each token in a log message can be either a constant (common part or keyword) or a variable (dynamic number or parameter). You must abstract the variables with <*> and remain the constants as the same to extract the corresponding template. You must print the results following the format below:
Log message: [BEGIN] ... [END]
Log template: [BEGIN] ... [END]
<</SYS>>

Log message: [BEGIN] CE sym 20, at 0x1438f9e0, mask 0x40 [END] [/INST] Log message: [BEGIN] CE sym 20, at 0x1438f9e0, mask 0x40 [END]
Log template: [BEGIN] CE sym <num>, at <hex>, mask <hex> [END]
Where:
* <num> is a placeholder for a numerical value (in this case, 20)
* <hex> is a placeholder for a hexadecimal value (in this case, 0x1438f9e0)
* <hex> is a placeholder for another hexadecimal value (in this case, 0x40)</s><s>[INST] Log message: [BEGIN] {input} [END] [/INST]
